ER24&#8217;s Air Angel touched down at the Middelburg Fire Brigade, picking up their second patient for the day. The patient, a man with head injuries, was transported from Life Midmed in Middelburg to a hospital in Gauteng.This after a horror accident this morning on the Stoffberg Road (R555) which left three people dead and six seriously injured.One of the six seriously injured patients, a female who sustained serious head injuries, is in a critical condition.The accident happened when a pickup, believed to belong to a mine contractor, rear-ended a Nissan 1400 bakkie carrying passengers on the back in a canopy.See a video of the accident scene, and how civilians offer help to paramedics here:&nbsp;Read previous story and see photos of accident scene here:Warning &#8211; Graphic content: Horror accident on R555